[center][size=6][b]Spell Sword[/b][/size]
[i]Fire a clone of your weapon — carrying your spell — straight out the blade.[/i][/center]

[line]

[size=4][b]What it does[/b][/size]
Hold a weapon or shield and [b]click the imbue/spell button[/b] to launch a clone of it:
[list]
[*][b]Weapons[/b] shoot out along the blade tip, toward whatever you're pointing at.
[*][b]Shields[/b] fly out in the direction your hand is pointing.
[/list]
The clone carries your [b]current imbue[/b] (fire, lightning, gravity…). Imbue your blade or just have a spell selected on that hand and the clone flies out enchanted. No spell? It's a plain clone.

[size=4][b]Features[/b][/size]
[list]
[*][b]Imbue-aware[/b] — the clone inherits your blade's active imbue, or the spell selected on that hand.
[*][b]Penetrates[/b] — clones are flagged as thrown, so they stab and stick like a real throw.
[*][b]Fast & weight-independent[/b] — a battleaxe clone flies as fast as a dagger clone.
[*][b]Shield support[/b] — shields launch in the direction your hand points.
[*][b]Configurable[/b] — an in-game options menu lets you pick which items it works on.
[*][b]Lightweight[/b] — pure code mod using only the game's own assets. No AssetBundles.
[/list]

[size=4][b]How to use[/b][/size]
[list=1]
[*]Grab a weapon or shield.
[*](Optional) Select or imbue a spell on that hand for an elemental clone.
[*][b]Click the spell/imbue button[/b] — a clone fires out, point-first (shields fire where your hand points).
[/list]

[size=4][b]Configuration[/b][/size]
Open [b]Options → Mods[/b] in-game:
[list]
[*][b]Spell Sword Enabled[/b] — master on/off.
[*][b]Active On[/b] — Short sword only · All swords · All daggers · Swords & daggers · All weapons · All weapons & tools · All shields · Any held item.
[/list]

[size=4][b]Installation[/b][/size]
[list=1]
[*]Download the file and extract it.
[*]Copy the [b]SpellSword[/b] folder into:
[code]...\steamapps\common\Blade & Sorcery\BladeAndSorcery_Data\StreamingAssets\Mods\[/code]
[*]Start (or restart) the game.
[/list]
To uninstall, delete the [b]SpellSword[/b] folder and restart.

[size=4][b]Compatibility[/b][/size]
[list]
[*]Blade & Sorcery [b]PCVR[/b], game version [b]1.0.0.0[/b]. (Not for Nomad / Quest.)
[*]Uses only stock content, so it won't clash with other mods' assets.
[/list]

[size=4][b]Source & issues[/b][/size]
Open source (MIT). Code, changelog, and bug reports:
[url=https://github.com/tony-zeidan/blade-and-sorcery-spell-sword]github.com/tony-zeidan/blade-and-sorcery-spell-sword[/url]

